				<th>Title of Invention</th>
				<td><h1 style="font-size:large;">METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR INTERLEAVING SINGAL BITS IN A DIGITAL AUDIO BROADCASTING SYSTEM A METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR INTERLEAVING BITS OF A DOGITAL SINGNAL REPRESENTATIVE OF DATA AND?OR AUDIO IN A DIGITAK AUDIO BROADCASTING SYSTEM</h1></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<th>Abstract</th>
				<td>This invention provides a method for interleaving bits of a digital signal representative of data and/or audio in a digital audio broadcasting system, the method comprising the step of: writing a plurality of bits of the digital signal to a matrix (Fig.22): and reading the bits from the matrix, wherein at least one of the writing and reading steps follows a non-sequential addressing scheme. Apparatus for transmiting the interleaved bits and apparatus for receiving and deinterleaving the bits are also provided.</td>
			</tr>
		</table>

