deinterleaving and receiving apparatus is shown as the receiver shown in FIG. 1.<br>
[0211] While the present invention has been described in terms of its preferred<br>
embodiment, it will be understood by those skilled in the art that various modifications can be<br>
made to the disclosed embodiment without departing from the scope of the invention as set<br>
forth in the claims.<br>
WE CLAIM:<br>
1. A method for interleaving bits of a digital signal representative<br>
of data and/or audio in a digital audio broadcasting system, the method comprising<br>
the step of:<br>
writing a plurality of bits of the digital signal to an internal matrix;<br>
reading the bits from the internal matrix, wherein at least one of the<br>
writing and reading steps follows a non-sequential addressing scheme; and<br>
writing the bits to an output matrix.<br>
2. The method as claimed in claim 1, wherein the number of bits<br>
in the output matrix is equal to the number of bits in a transfer frame of IN digital<br>
signal.<br>
3. The method as claimed in claim 1, wherein the bits in the<br>
internal matrix are arranged in a plurality of partitions.<br>
4. The method as claimed in claim 3, wherein each of the<br>
partitions comprises a plurality of blocks.<br>
5. The method as claimed in claim 3, wherein each of the<br>
partitions comprises a group of the bits representative of a logical channel.<br>
6. The method as claimed in claim 5, wherein the bits in each<br>
logical channel are scrambled.<br>
7. A method of broadcasting digital information representative of<br>
data and/or audio in a digital audio broadcasting system, the method comprising<br>
the steps of:<br>
receiving a plurality of bits of a digital signal to be transmitted;<br>
writing the bits to an internal matrix;<br>
reading the bits from the internal matrix, wherein at least one of the<br>
writing and reading steps follows a non-sequential addressing schema;<br>
writing the bits to an output matrix;<br>
mapping the bits to a plurality of carrier signals; and<br>
transmitting the carrier signals.<br>
8. The method as claimed in claim 7, wherein the number of bits<br>
in the output matrix is equal to the number of bits in a transfer frame of the digital<br>
signal.<br>
9. The method of claim 7, wherein the bits in the internal matrix<br>
are arranged in a plurality of partitions.<br>
10. The method as claimed in claim 9, wherein each of the<br>
partitions comprises a plurality of blocks.<br>
11. The method as claimed in claim 9, wherein each of the<br>
partitions comprises a group of the bits representative of a logical channel.<br>
12. The method as claimed in claim 11, wherein the bits in each<br>
logical channel are scrambled.<br>
13. The method as claimed in claim 7, further comprising the<br>
step of:<br>
channel coding the bits prior to the step of writing the bits of the<br>
digital signal to the internal matrix.<br>
14. The method as claimed In claim 7, further comprising the<br>
step of:<br>
scrambling the bits prior to the step of writing the bits of the digital<br>
signal to the internal matrix.<br>
15. An apparatus for interleaving bits of a digital signal<br>
representative of data and/or audio in a digital audio broadcasting system, the<br>
apparatus comprising:<br>
means (12,14,16) for receiving a plurality of bits of a digital signal<br>
to be transmitted; and<br>
means (116) for writing the bits to an internal matrix; reading the<br>
bits from the internal matrix, wherein at least one of the means for writing and the<br>
means for reading follows a non-sequential addressing scheme; and writing the bte<br>
to an output matrix.<br>
16. The apparatus as claimed in claim 15, wherein the number of<br>
bits in the output matrix is equal to the number of bits in a transfer frame of the<br>
digital signal.<br>
17. The apparatus of claim 15, wherein the bits in the internal<br>
matrix are arranged in a plurality of partitions.<br>
18. The apparatus as claimed in claim 17, wherein each of the<br>
partitions comprises a plurality of blocks.<br>
19. The apparatus as claimed in claim 17, wherein each of the<br>
partitions comprises a group of the bits representative of a logical channel.<br>
20. The apparatus as claimed in claim 19, wherein the bits in each<br>
logical channel are scrambled.<br>
21. An apparatus of broadcasting digital information<br>
representative of data and/or audio in a digital audio broadcasting system, the<br>
apparatus comprising:<br>
means (12,14,16) for receiving a plurality of bits of a digital signal<br>
to be transmitted;<br>
means (116) for writing the bite of the digital signal to an internal<br>
matrix; for reading the bits from the internal matrix, wherein at least one of the<br>
means for writing and the means for reading follows a non-sequential addressing<br>
scheme; and for writing the bits to an output matrix;<br>
means (170) for mapping the bits to a plurality of carrier signals; and<br>
means (174) for transmitting the carrier signals.<br>
22. The apparatus as claimed in claim 21, wherein the number of<br>
bits in the output matrix is equal to the number of bits in one of the transfer<br>
frames.<br>
23. The apparatus as claimed in claim 21, wherein the bits in the<br>
internal matrix are arranged in a plurality of partitions.<br>
24. The apparatus as claimed in claim 23, wherein each of the<br>
partitions comprises a plurality of blocks.<br>
25. The apparatus as claimed in claim 23, wherein each of the<br>
partitions comprises a group of the bits representative of a logical channel.<br>
26. The apparatus as claimed in claim 25, wherein the bits in each<br>
logical channel are scrambled.<br>
27. The apparatus as claimed in claim 21, further comprising:<br>
means (164) for channel coding the bite prior to the step of writing<br>
the bits of the digital signal to the internal matrix.<br>
28. The apparatus as claimed in claim 21, further comprising:<br>
means (162) for scrambling the bite prior to the step of writing the<br>
bite of the digital signal to the internal matrix.<br>
29. A method of receiving digital information representative of<br>
data and/or audio in a digital audio broadcasting system, the method comprising<br>
the steps of:<br>
receiving a plurality of received bits of a digital signal;<br>
writing the bits to an internal matrix;<br>
reading the bits from the internal matrix, wherein at least one of the<br>
means for writing and means for reading follows a non-sequential addressing<br>
scheme;<br>
writing the read bits to an output matrix; and<br>
using the read bits to produce an output signal.<br>
30. The method as claimed in claim 29, wherein the number of<br>
bits in the output matrix is equal to the number of bits in a transfer frame of the<br>
digital signal.<br>
31. An apparatus for receiving digital information representative of<br>
data and/or audio in a digital audio broadcasting system, the apparatus comprising:<br>
a receiver (48) for receiving a plurality of bits of a digital signal; for<br>
writing the bits of the digital signal to an internal matrix; for reading the bits from<br>
the internal matrix, wherein at least one of the means for writing and means for<br>
reading follows a non-sequential addressing scheme; for writing the bits of the<br>
digital signal to an output matrix; and for using the read bits to produce an output<br>
signal.<br>
32. The apparatus as claimed in claim 31, wherein the number<br>
of bits in the output matrix is equal to the number of bits in one of the transfer<br>
frames.<br>
This invention provides a method for interleaving bits of a digital signal representative of data and/or audio in a digital<br>
audio broadcasting system, the method comprising the step of: writing a plurality of bits of the digital signal to a matrix (Fig.22): and<br>
reading the bits from the matrix, wherein at least one of the writing and reading steps follows a non-sequential addressing scheme.<br>
Apparatus for transmiting the interleaved bits and apparatus for receiving and deinterleaving the bits are also provided.</td>
			</tr>
		</table>	
